# TEST BINARY RULES

## Architecture
The test suite is embedded in the same binary as the server/main.
Activated by `--test` CLI flag. Three sequential phases:

  Phase 1 (f49): Unit — core crate functions directly, no I/O, no processes
  Phase 2 (f50): Integration — real DB in temp dirs, no network
  Phase 3 (f51): HTTP — real server on random port, real HTTP requests

## Test Isolation
- Each integration test owns its TempDir and DB — no shared state
- HTTP tests bind to random port (OS-assigned)
- No test depends on previous test state
- No external network; set env in test setup
- TempDir cleanup automatic via Drop

## Test Result
Every test returns a result with: name, passed/failed, duration, optional message.
Aggregator exits 0 or 1 based on aggregate pass/fail.
Use colored output (PASS green, FAIL red) for readability.

## HTTP Test Concept
For f51: spawn real server in background, get base URL and HTTP client with cookie store.
Make real requests; verify status and content. Server runs as tokio task, not child process.

## What Tests Validate
Each test exercises REAL code paths — no mocks for mock's sake:
- Crypto: real encrypt/decrypt, verify round-trip and tamper rejection
- Password: real hash/verify
- Session: real create/validate, UUID and expiry
- DB: real queries, verify persistence
- HTTP: real requests, verify status codes and body content
